<example id="fs-id1604350">
<exercise id="fs-id1604353"><problem id="fs-id1605798">
<para id="fs-id1605800">Graph the equation <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>−1</m:mn><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1605821">
<title>Solution</title>
<para id="fs-id1605826">Find three points that are solutions to the equation.</para>
<para id="fs-id1605830">First, solve the equation for <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
<para id="fs-id1171103271744"><m:math><m:mtable><m:mtr><m:mtd columnalign="right"><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:mtd><m:mtd><m:mo>=</m:mo></m:mtd><m:mtd columnalign="left"><m:mn>−1</m:mn></m:mtd></m:mtr>
<m:mtr><m:mtd columnalign="right"><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:mtd><m:mtd><m:mo>=</m:mo></m:mtd><m:mtd columnalign="left"><m:mn>−3</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mtd></m:mtr></m:mtable></m:math></para><para id="fs-id1600966">We’ll let <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math> be <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> and <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>−1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> to find three points. The ordered pairs are shown in the table. Plot the points, check that they line up, and draw the line.</para>
<table id="fs-id1600993" class="unnumbered" summary="This table it titled y = -3 x - 1. It has 4 rows and 3 columns. The first row is a header row and it labels each column “x”, “y”, and  “ordered pair x, y”. Under the column “x” are the values  -1, 0, and 1, which are shown in blue. Under the column “y” are the values  2, -1, and -4. Under the column “ordered pair x, y” are the values “ordered pair -1,  2”, “ordered pair 0, -1”, and “ordered pair 1, -4”."><label/>
<tgroup cols="3">
<colspec colnum="1" colname="c1"/>
<colspec colnum="2" colname="c2"/>
<colspec colnum="3" colname="c3"/>
<thead><row valign="top">
<entry align="center" namest="c1" nameend="c3"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>−3</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math></entry>
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:math></entry>
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>


<row valign="top">
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:math></entry>
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>−1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></entry>
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>−1</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:math></entry>
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>−4</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></entry>
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>−4</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>−1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></entry>
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:math></entry>
<entry align="left"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>−1</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></entry>
</row>
</tbody>
