<image mime-type="image/jpeg" src="../../media/CNX_BMath_Figure_11_02_012.jpg"/>
</media>
<para id="fs-id1603836">If you can choose any three points to graph a line, how will you know if your graph matches the one shown in the answers in the book? If the points where the graphs cross the <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mtext>-</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math> and <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>-axes are the same, the graphs match.</para></solution>
</exercise>
</example>
<note id="fs-id1603861" class="try">
<exercise id="fs-id1603864">
<problem id="fs-id1603867">
<para id="fs-id1603869">Graph each equation: <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</problem>
