<exercise id="fs-id1609995">
<problem id="fs-id1609997">
<para id="fs-id1610000"><emphasis effect="bold">Motor home cost</emphasis> The Robinsons rented a motor home for one week to go on vacation. It cost them <m:math><m:mrow><m:mtext>$594</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math> plus <m:math><m:mrow><m:mtext>$0.32</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math> per mile to rent the motor home, so the linear equation <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>594</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>0.32</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math> gives the cost, <m:math><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>,</m:mo></m:math> for driving <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math> miles. Calculate the rental cost for driving <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>400</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>800</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mtext>and</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mn>1,200</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> miles, and then graph the line.</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1610062">
<para id="fs-id1610064"><newline/>
<media id="fs-id1610068" alt="The graph shows the x y-coordinate plane. The x-axis runs from 0 to 1000. The y-axis runs from 0 to 1200. A line passes through the points “ordered pair 0,  594” and “ordered pair 800, 850”.">
<image mime-type="image/jpeg" src="../../media/CNX_BMath_Figure_11_02_270_img.jpg"/>
</media><newline/>
$722, $850, $978</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id1610081">
