<para id="fs-id1610085"><emphasis effect="bold">Weekly earning</emphasis> At the art gallery where he works, Salvador gets paid <m:math><m:mrow><m:mtext>$200</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math> per week plus <m:math><m:mrow><m:mtext>15%</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math> of the sales he makes, so the equation <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>200</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>0.15</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math> gives the amount <m:math><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:math> he earns for selling <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math> dollars of artwork. Calculate the amount Salvador earns for selling <m:math><m:mrow><m:mtext>$900, $1,600</m:mtext><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mtext>and</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mtext>$2,000</m:mtext><m:mo>,</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> and then graph the line.</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
