<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1610210">
<term>horizontal line</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1610215">A horizontal line is the graph of an equation that can be written in the form <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>b</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>. The line passes through the <emphasis effect="italics">y-</emphasis>axis at <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mi>b</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1610267">
<term>vertical line</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1610272">A vertical line is the graph of an equation that can be written in the form <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>a</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>. The line passes through the <emphasis effect="italics">x-</emphasis>axis at <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mi>a</m:mi><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
